    'gallery_2015' => 'Solo International Performing Arts (SIPA) 2015 was an annual event celebrating the beauty of performing arts from various parts of the world. Held at Benteng Vastenburg, Solo, SIPA 2015 presented stirring performances with the theme <strong><em>"Live in the Contemporary World".</em></strong> Taking place on September 10, 11, and 12, 2015, the event featured artworks reflecting modern life dynamics and cultural challenges in the contemporary era. Featuring Fajar Satriadi as the mascot, SIPA 2015 aimed to bridge artworks that respond to the times, and to foster communication across individuals, communities, and nations. With the spirit of innovation, freedom of expression, and global harmony, SIPA became a platform uniting the world through art.',
