    'gallery_2019' => 'Solo International Performing Arts (SIPA) 2019 was an annual event celebrating the beauty of performing arts from various parts of the world. Held at Benteng Vastenburg, Solo, SIPA 2019 presented stirring performances with the theme <strong><em>"Arts as a Social Action".</em></strong> Through this stage, art was positioned not only as an aesthetic expression but also as a concrete response to social issues such as environment, gender, and politics. Featuring Elizabeth Sudira as the mascot, SIPA 2019 aimed to bridge artworks that voiced concern and build communication across individuals, communities, and nations. In the spirit of peace, harmony, and mutual respect, SIPA served as a platform uniting the world through art.',
